---
name: kie-voiceover
description: Generate a voiceover from a script using ElevenLabs via the kie.ai API. Use when the user asks to generate a voiceover, narration, or text-to-speech. Also use when the user invokes /kie-voiceover directly.
---

Generate a voiceover via the kie.ai ElevenLabs text-to-speech API.

## Step 1 — Parse arguments

The user's args string is the script text. Accept these optional flags:
- `--voice <id>` — ElevenLabs voice ID (default: `Lp2NZJAfG4zDynNcYPSz`)
- `--model <id>` — TTS model (default: `elevenlabs/text-to-speech-turbo-2-5`). Options: `elevenlabs/text-to-speech-turbo-2-5`, `elevenlabs/text-to-speech-multilingual-v2`
- `--speed <n>` — playback rate 0.7–1.2 (default: `1`)
- `--stability <n>` — voice consistency 0–1 (default: `0.5`)
- `--lang <code>` — ISO 639-1 language code (default: omit for auto-detect)
- `--prev-text <text>` — text from the previous generation for voice continuity
- `--next-text <text>` — text that follows this generation for voice continuity

**Voice continuity note:** kie.ai's ElevenLabs TTS uses `previous_text` and `next_text` (surrounding script context) to maintain consistent delivery across multiple generations. Pass the preceding segment as `--prev-text` and the following segment as `--next-text` when generating multi-part voiceovers.

## Step 2 — Check API key

Verify `KIE_API_KEY` is set. If not, tell the user to run: `export KIE_API_KEY=your_key_here`

## Step 3 — Submit the task

```bash
curl -s -X POST https://api.kie.ai/api/v1/jobs/createTask \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $KIE_API_KEY" \
  -d '{
    "model": "<model>",
    "input": {
      "text": "<script>",
      "voice": "<voice_id>",
      "stability": <stability>,
      "similarity_boost": 0.75,
      "speed": <speed>,
      "previous_text": "<prev_text>",
      "next_text": "<next_text>"
    }
  }'
```

Omit `language_code` unless `--lang` was specified. Omit `previous_text` and `next_text` unless the corresponding flags were provided.

Parse the response. If `code` is not `200`, show `msg` and stop. Extract `data.taskId`.

## Step 4 — Poll for completion

Poll every 8 seconds:

```bash
curl -s "https://api.kie.ai/api/v1/jobs/recordInfo?taskId=<taskId>" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $KIE_API_KEY"
```

`data.state` values: `waiting` → `queuing` → `generating` → `success` / `fail`

Show status updates. If `state` is `fail`, show `data.failMsg` and stop.

## Step 5 — Return result

When `state` is `success`, parse `data.resultJson` as JSON and extract the audio URL from `resultUrls[0]`.

Display:
- The audio URL as a clickable link
- Voice ID and model used
- Task ID for reference

Ask if the user wants to download locally. If yes:

```bash
curl -L -o ~/Downloads/"voiceover-$(date +%Y%m%d-%H%M%S).mp3" "<audio_url>"
```

Report the saved path.
